<p id="mwAew">If all the forces acting on a particle are conservative, and <i id="mwAe0">E</i><sub id="mwAe4">p</sub> is the total potential energy (which is defined as a work of involved forces to rearrange mutual positions of bodies), obtained by summing the potential energies corresponding to each force</p>
<dl id="mwAe8"><dd id="mwAfA"><span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt150" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":"\\mathbf{F} \\cdot \\Delta \\mathbf{r} = - \\mathbf{\\nabla} E_\\mathrm{p} \\cdot \\Delta \\mathbf{r} = - \\Delta E_\\mathrm{p} \\, ."}}' id="mwAfE"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \mathbf {F} \cdot \Delta \mathbf {r} =-\mathbf {\nabla } E_{\mathrm {p} }\cdot \Delta \mathbf {r} =-\Delta E_{\mathrm {p} }\,.}">
